on \u2013 [[North Carolina Central Eagles football|North Carolina Central]]<br>\nGreat Lakes Intercollegiate Athletic Conference \u2013 [[Grand Valley State Lakers football|Grand Valley State]]<br>\nGreat Northwest Athletic Conference \u2013 [[Central Washington Wildcats football|Central Washington]]<br>\nGulf South Conference \u2013 [[Central Arkansas Bears football|Central Arkansas]]<br>\nLone Star Conference \u2013 [[West Texas A&M Buffaloes football|West Texas A&M]]<br>\nMid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association \u2013 [[Washburn Ichabods football|Washburn]]<br>\nNorth Central Conference \u2013 [[Minnesota\u2013Duluth Bulldogs football|Minnesota\u2013Duluth]], [[Nebraska\u2013Omaha Mavericks football|Nebraska\u2013Omaha]], [[North Dakota Fighting Sioux football|North Dakota]], and [[South Dakota Coyotes football|South Dakota]]<br>\nNortheast-10 Conference \u2013 [[LIU Post Pioneers football|C.W. Post]]<br>\nNorthern Sun Intercollegiate Conference \u2013 [[Concordia Golden Bears football|Concordia\u2013Saint Paul]] and [[Winona State Warriors football|Winona State]]<br>\nPennsylvania State Athletic Conference \u2013 [[Bloomsburg Huskies football|Bloomsburg]] (East), [[California Vulcans football|California (PA)]] and [[Edinboro Fighting Scots football|Edinboro]] (West)<br>\nRocky Mountain Athletic Conference \u2013 [[Nebraska\u2013Kearney Lopers football|Nebraska\u2013Kearney]]<br>\nSouth Atlantic Conference \u2013 [[Presbyterian Blue Hose football|Presbyterian]]<br>\nSouthern Intercollegiate Athletic Conference \u2013 [[Albany State Golden Rams football|Albany State]]<br>\nWest Virginia Intercollegiate Athletic Conference \u2013 [[Shepherd Rams football|Shepherd]]\n|}\n\n==Postseason==\n{{Infobox NCAA Football Tournament |\n| Division=[[NCAA Division II|II]]\n| Year=2005\n| Image=\n| ImageSize=\n| Caption=\n| Teams=24\n| Stadium=[[Braly Municipal Stadium]]\n| Location=[[Florence, Alabama|Florence, AL]]\n| Champions= [[Grand Valley State Lakers football|G