gh School ([[Hillsville, Virginia]]).\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070203233356/http://www.ccpsd.k12.va.us/schpages/cchs/index.htm CCHS Official Site]\n\n==Communities==\n===Town===\n*[[Hillsville, Virginia|Hillsville]]\n\n===Census-designated places===\n*[[Cana, Virginia|Cana]]\n*[[Fancy Gap, Virginia|Fancy Gap]]\n*[[Woodlawn, Carroll County, Virginia|Woodlawn]]\n\n===Other unincorporated communities===\n*[[Austinville, Virginia|Austinville]]\n*[[Dugspur, Virginia|Dugspur]]\n*[[Lambsburg, Virginia|Lambsburg]]\n*[[Laurel Fork, Virginia|Laurel Fork]]\n*[[Sylvatus, Virginia|Sylvatus]]\n\n==Notable residents==\n* [[Floyd Allen]]  (1856-1913) &ndash; landowner and chief patriarch of the powerful Allen clan; convicted and executed for murder after sensational 1912 [[Hillsville, Virginia|Hillsville]] courthouse shootout that killed five people including Circuit Judge Thornton Massie, Commonwealth's Attorney William Foster, and sheriff Lewis Webb.\n* [[Doc Ayers]] &ndash; [[Major League Baseball]] pitcher, [[Washington Senators (1901\u201360)|Washington Senators]], [[Detroit Tigers]]\n* [[Kylene Barker]] &ndash; [[Miss America 1979]]\n* [[Frank Beamer]] &ndash; Head football coach at [[Virginia Tech]] - [[List of college football coaches with 200 wins]]\n* [[George Lafayette Carter]] &ndash; land, railroad entrepreneur, instrumental in the establishment of [[East Tennessee State University]]\n* [[Charles B. Morris]] (1931-1996) &ndash; U.S. Army, Awarded the [[Medal of Honor]], December 14, 1967\n* [[Ernest Stoneman]]  (1893\u20131968) &ndash; early country music recording artist\n\n==See also==\n*[[National Register of Historic Places listings in Carroll County, Virginia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{osmrelation|2532620}}\n*[http://www.graysoncarrollgalaxva.com Grayson Carroll Galax VA Directory]\n*[http://carrollcountyva.org/index.php/govt_template/ County government website]\n\n{{Geographic Location\n|Centre    = Carroll County, Vir